article.headline: North Dakota State, behind Stick, throttles Wofford in FCS quarters

images.name: Stick weighs in on North Dakota State's 42-10 win over Wofford
images.caption: Easton Stick says the Bison's play-action worked well because they did a "good job establishing the run game early."

article.linkText: North Dakota State, behind Stick, throttles Wofford in FCS quarters
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Easton Stick threw for three first-half touchdowns and ran for another in the second half and second-seeded North Dakota State rolled to a 42-10 win over seventh-seeded Wofford in the FCS quarterfinals on Saturday. Bruce Anderson also ran for two scores in the first half for the Bison (12-1), who plays Sam Houston State in the semifinals next weekend at home. Stick completed 9 of 10 passes in the first half for 157 yards with touchdowns to Connor Wentz (48 yards), Seth Wilson (18 yards) and Jeff Illies (4 yards). The Bison piled up 265 yards and held Wofford to 95 with just four first downs, two coming on fourth down conversions. The Terriers got a field goal on their initial possession and a touchdown after a fumble recovery gave them a short field. Stick's 7-yard run accounted for the only points in the second half. NDSU, which won five-straight titles before losing to eventual champion James Madison in the semifinals last year, piled up 261 yards on the ground and 464 yards of total offense. While the Bison were seven yards shy of their season average on the ground, they held the Terriers (10-3) to 134, 120 below their average. Wofford ended up with eight first downs and 177 yards, going 1 of 12 on third down.

videos.headline: Wofford picks up 38 yards on 4th down
videos.description: The Terriers elect to go for it on 4th down and Blake Morgan finds a huge hole for a 38-yard gain.

videos.headline: Wentz's TD catch puts North Dakota State on the board
videos.description: Easton Stick finds Connor Wentz, the cousin of former NDSU QB and current Eagles star Carson Wentz, along the sideline for a 48-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: NDSU gets into Wofford territory with big gain
videos.description: Easton Stick throws a strike to RJ Urzendowski for a 44-yard catch-and-run.

videos.headline: NDSU's Wilson makes acrobatic 18-yard TD grab
videos.description: Easton Stick finds Seth Wilson open in the end zone for an 18-yard touchdown to give North Dakota State a 14-3 lead in the opening quarter.

videos.headline: NDSU player accidentally runs into ball during snap
videos.description: With North Dakota State in the shotgun, Ty Brooks runs in front of the ball as it's snapped, causing a loose ball and a recovery for Wofford.

videos.headline: Stoddard punches it in for Wofford TD
videos.description: Andre Stoddard runs up the middle for a 3-yard score on 4th down to log Wofford's first touchdown of the game.

videos.headline: NDSU's Brooks breaks tackles for 33-yard gain
videos.description: Ty Brooks bounces to the outside and evades tackles for a 33-yard run to Wofford's 24-yard line.

videos.headline: Anderson scores NDSU's third first-half TD
videos.description: Bruce Anderson runs up the gut for a 1-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: NDSU gets 1st-and-goal after fumble recovery
videos.description: Robbie Grimsley scoops up the loose ball and returns it 21 yards to Wofford's 3-yard line.

videos.headline: NDSU's Stick throws third TD pass
videos.description: Easton Stick finds Jeff Illies on the outside for a 4-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: NDSU recovers another fumble
videos.description: Brandon Brown coughs up the football during the kickoff return and Jabril Cox recovers the football with good field position.

videos.headline: NDSU's Anderson scores second first-half TD
videos.description: Bruce Anderson runs up the middle for a 5-yard touchdown to increase North Dakota State's lead over Wofford to 35-10 going into the half.

videos.headline: Stick escapes pressure for NDSU TD
videos.description: Easton Stick takes it himself for a 7-yard touchdown as North Dakota State takes a dominating 42-10 lead over Wofford.
